    <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
    <div class="quick-answer">
      <h3>Quick Answer</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>For men 160–210 lbs, 120g is a solid, research-backed daily target</li>
        <li>It clears the 1.2g/kg threshold that supports muscle maintenance after 40</li>
        <li>For men over 220 lbs or serious lifters, 120g is the floor — not the ceiling</li>
        <li>Most men eating 60–70g/day need to close a 50g gap, not a 100g gap</li>
        <li>The gap is real — but it's closable. Visibility is what's missing.</li>
      </ul>
