      <div class="author-avatar">R</div>
      <p><strong>Robert, founder of SnapProtein.</strong> I'm 64 and have been tracking protein seriously for years. I built this app because I kept losing track of where I stood each day — not because I didn't care, but because I couldn't see the number clearly. That's the problem 120g solves.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">

      <p>
        If you've landed here, you already know the number. You've probably seen it in a post, heard it from someone, or read it somewhere on this site. The question isn't what 120g looks like — <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/what-120g-protein-looks-like/">we covered exactly what a 120g day looks like in detail</a>. The question is whether 120g is the right target <em>for you specifically</em>.
      </p>

      <p>
        The short answer: for most men over 40, yes. But "most" isn't everyone. Here's how to know which group you're in.
      </p>

