          <div class="wc-flag">✓ Well above optimal</div>
          <div class="wc-top">160 lbs (73 kg)</div>
          <div class="wc-grams">120g</div>
          <div class="wc-note">Target: ~88g/day at 1.2g/kg. You're 32g over. Strong position for muscle maintenance and growth.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="weight-card flag-good">
          <div class="wc-flag">✓ Above optimal</div>
          <div class="wc-top">180 lbs (82 kg)</div>
          <div class="wc-grams">120g</div>
          <div class="wc-note">Target: ~98g/day. You're comfortably above the threshold. 120g is the right number here.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="weight-card flag-good">
          <div class="wc-flag">✓ Solidly at optimal</div>
          <div class="wc-top">200 lbs (91 kg)</div>
          <div class="wc-grams">120g</div>
          <div class="wc-note">Target: ~109g/day. 120g clears the bar. You're in the optimal zone for a man your size.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="weight-card flag-ok">
          <div class="wc-flag">⚠ Right at the line</div>
          <div class="wc-top">220 lbs (100 kg)</div>
          <div class="wc-grams">120g</div>
          <div class="wc-note">Target: ~120g/day. You're exactly at the 1.2g/kg threshold. Aim for 130–140g to give yourself a buffer.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="weight-card flag-low">
          <div class="wc-flag">↑ Needs more</div>
          <div class="wc-top">240 lbs (109 kg)</div>
          <div class="wc-grams">120g</div>
          <div class="wc-note">Target: ~131g/day. At this weight, 120g falls short. 140–150g is a more appropriate daily target.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="weight-card flag-low">
          <div class="wc-flag">↑ Floor, not ceiling</div>
          <div class="wc-top">260+ lbs (118+ kg)</div>
          <div class="wc-grams">120g</div>
          <div class="wc-note">Target: ~141g+. Bigger frame, bigger protein needs. 120g is a starting point, not your number.</div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p>
        If your weight lands in the 160–210 lb range — which covers the majority of men over 40 — 120g is a strong, well-grounded target. Not a lowball. Not a compromise. The research-backed number for your size.
      </p>

      <div class="link-box">
        <strong>Go Deeper</strong>
